rComments: I think he is a really good and fair prof.  Knows his stuff

Very nice professor! Very understanding if you have late papers, homework...  Not much work at all, just attend all lectures and take notes. Class tend to be boring though, especially on days when we had terrible guest speakers.
Several words come to mind when thinking about Prof Ono. Brilliant is not one of them.
This professor is a genius who is excellent at explaining difficult concepts in a clear way.

I have learned a LOT under Ono.  He is extremely intelligent and knows what he's talking about.  He is really nice and will work with you.  Also is open minded and patient, even with really difficult people.
Take this course only if you are an naive fool willing to be taught by a naive fool.  But it does provide an excellant opportunity to read the DI, sleep, or otherwise recreate.
